9. Use a Web Application Firewall (WAF)

•	Deploy a WAF to filter and monitor HTTP traffic for malicious activity.

10. Regularly Update and Patch
•	Keep your Docker images, Kubernetes cluster, and dependencies up to date to patch known vulnerabilities.

11. Use Image Scanning
•	Scan Docker images for vulnerabilities using tools like Trivy, Aqua Security, or Clair.
---
12. Isolate Sensitive Workloads
•	Use Kubernetes Namespaces to isolate sensitive workloads and apply stricter security policies.
---
13. Perform Regular Security Audits
•	Use tools like Kube-bench and Kube-hunter to audit your Kubernetes cluster for security issues.